  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points. A comprehensive UQ campaign was executed and sensitivity rankings were discussed in the validation report narrative; all 13 credibility factors have been assessed. Decision: Accepted with conditions documented in the decision record.",
